= Extracted Lists
<extracted-lists>
The list environments below are extracted from arXiv LaTeX source and
wrapped for pdfLaTeX validation.

+ The adjoint representation of #mi(`{\cal G}_0`) decomposes into rank
  #mi(`\cal
  G`) multiplets of the subalgebra #mi(`\cal S`) ([su2]).

+ The representation of #mi(`{\cal G}_0`) in #mi(`{\cal G}_1`) also
  decomposes into rank #mi(`\cal G`) #mi(`\cal S`)-multiplets.

+ After the gauge fixing there is a one to one correspondence between
  remaining currents and #mi(`\cal S`)-multiplets in the adjoint of
  #mi(`\cal G`).

+ The number of remaining currents with integer and half integer height
  is the same and equal to the rank of #mi(`\cal G`).

+ The conformal spin, w.r.t. #mi(`L(x)`), of the remaining current
  associated to the #mi(`\cal S`)-multiplet with highest weight #mi(`j`)
  is #mi(`(j+1)`).
